    "id": "unbounded-request-spawns-subprocess",
    "severity": "MEDIUM",
    "category": "dos-surface",
    "location": "scripts/ai_agent_bridge/openai_proxy.py:41",
    "description": "The chat request model accepts an unbounded `messages` list with unbounded string content, and each accepted request starts a backend subprocess that may run for up to 120 seconds. A client can submit very large prompts or many-message payloads to consume memory, CPU, process slots, and backend quota; the proxy should enforce request and prompt size limits before flattening and dispatching to local CLIs."
  },
  {
    "id": "prompt-in-process-argv",
    "severity": "MEDIUM",
    "category": "security",
    "location": "scripts/ai_agent_bridge/openai_proxy.py:165",
    "description": "The Gemini, Claude, and Hermes backends pass the full user prompt as command-line arguments (`--prompt=...`, positional prompt, or `--oneshot=...`). This exposes potentially sensitive request content through local process listings and also makes large requests fail at OS argument-length limits; these backends should pass prompt content through stdin or a temporary file with controlled permissions."
  },
  {
    "id": "stream-flag-silently-ignored",
    "severity": "LOW",
    "category": "spec-compliance",
    "location": "scripts/ai_agent_bridge/openai_proxy.py:38",
    "description": "The request model allows arbitrary extra OpenAI fields but the endpoint ignores `stream=true` and still returns a normal non-streaming completion with HTTP 200. OpenAI-compatible clients that request streaming will receive an unexpected response shape; the proxy should either implement streaming or reject `stream=true` with a clear unsupported-parameter error."
  }
